[[File:Steel dragon (Construction) icon.png|left]]
'''Steel dragons''' are powerful [[dragons]] found in the [[Brimhaven Dungeon]] and the [[Catacombs of Kourend]]. Steel dragons are the fourth strongest [[Metal dragons|metallic dragons]], behind [[mithril dragon|mithril]], [[adamant dragon|adamant]] and [[rune dragon]]s. They have a chance of dropping the [[draconic visage]]. Like their fellow metallic brethren, steel dragons can use long-range dragonfire in addition to using melee.

Completion of the [[Elite Karamja Diary]] notes the steel bars that they drop.

If they are fought without complete [[Dragonfire|dragonfire protection]], it is recommended to stay in melee range and use [[Protect from Melee]], to reduce the amount of dragonfire damage taken.

One Steel dragon is fought during [[Dragon Slayer II]].

